    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's what I explored and what the plan covers:\n\n### What I read\n- `packages/next/server.js` — the double-export pattern (object + named `exports.X = ...`) for CJS/ESM interop\n- `packages/next/server.d.ts` — re-exports from `next/dist/...` with `export type` for interfaces\n- `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/user-agent.ts` — the exact template to mirror\n- `packages/next/package.json` — the `files` array (lines 11–76), no `exports` field\n- `test/unit/web-runtime/user-agent.test.ts` — Jest test pattern using `describe`/`it`/`expect`\n\n### 5 files to create/modify\n\n| # | File | Action |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` | **Create** — `Geo` interface, `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries), `geoFromHeaders()`, `geo()`, `isInRegion()`, `geoDistance()` (Haversine). Zero external deps. |\n| 2 | `packages/next/geo.js` | **Create** — mirrors `server.js` exactly: object + named re-export pattern, requires from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo` |\n| 3 | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` | **Create** — mirrors `server.d.ts`: `export type { Geo }` + `export { geo, geoFromHeaders, isInRegion, geoDistance }` from `next/dist/...` |\n| 4 | `packages/next/package.json` | **Edit** — insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical G position in `files` array) |\n| 5 | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` | **Create** — Jest tests covering all functions, Cloudflare fallback, case-insensitive region check, NY→London distance (~5570 km ± 50 km), all 10 country codes |\n\n### Key design decisions\n- `headers.get()` returns `null` → `?? undefined` converts it to `undefined` to satisfy the `Geo` interface's optional fields under strict mode\n- Vercel header `x-vercel-ip-country` takes precedence over Cloudflare `cf-ipcountry` via `??` chaining\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` lookup uses `.toUpperCase()` for robustness against mixed-case input",
